1
00:01:46,160 --> 00:01:46,759
Sister|

2
00:01:46,759 --> 00:01:47,220
Sister.

3
00:01:59,400 --> 00:02:00,040
Sister.

4
00:02:00,200 --> 00:02:01,200
Why are you so late?

5
00:02:01,200 --> 00:02:02,000
Something happened.

6
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:02,840
What's the rush?

7
00:02:02,840 --> 00:02:03,500
Just say it.

8
00:02:03,560 --> 00:02:04,840
Fang just called

9
00:02:04,840 --> 00:02:06,880
and said someone died at Xinmai Hotel.

10
00:02:06,880 --> 00:02:08,479
The chief assigned this case to us.

11
00:02:08,479 --> 00:02:10,039
Shao is already on his way.

12
00:02:10,400 --> 00:02:10,919
Captain Zhuang,

13
00:02:10,919 --> 00:02:12,200
are we going to the scene?

14
00:02:12,200 --> 00:02:13,400
Can I go this time?

15
00:02:14,560 --> 00:02:16,090
Take good care of yourself.

16
00:02:18,079 --> 00:02:19,400
Then yes.

17
00:02:24,240 --> 00:02:25,440
Name and birthplace.

18
00:02:27,440 --> 00:02:28,640
Is everyone here?

19
00:02:34,360 --> 00:02:35,360
Where is Cheng Mo?

20
00:02:36,800 --> 00:02:38,160
He was just here.

21
00:02:38,440 --> 00:02:39,440
Forget about him.

22
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:40,800
Mia,

23
00:02:40,920 --> 00:02:42,520
what's wrong with your face?

24
00:02:45,880 --> 00:02:48,240
You two have been with Shao for so long.

25
00:02:48,240 --> 00:02:50,440
And you're still throwing up like this?

26
00:02:53,320 --> 00:02:54,000
Fang.

27
00:03:00,800 --> 00:03:02,060
Take a few more photos.

28
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:04,720
You'd better put this on.

29
00:03:04,720 --> 00:03:06,160
It really smells in here.

30
00:03:06,760 --> 00:03:08,360
With the body decomposed to this extent,

31
00:03:08,360 --> 00:03:10,620
the time of death is at least ten days ago.

32
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:11,960
Lin.

33
00:03:11,960 --> 00:03:13,240
It's not that we're cowards.

34
00:03:13,240 --> 00:03:14,360
Just put it on.

35
00:03:15,200 --> 00:03:16,200
No need.

36
00:03:16,400 --> 00:03:18,200
It's a piece of cake.

37
00:03:18,680 --> 00:03:21,000
According to the hotel's registration info,

38
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:22,240
the deceased is Li Ting.

39
00:03:22,240 --> 00:03:23,520
Male, 37.

40
00:03:23,520 --> 00:03:24,200
I've already checked.

41
00:03:24,200 --> 00:03:25,060
He was a writer.

42
00:03:25,200 --> 00:03:25,600
Look,

43
00:03:25,600 --> 00:03:28,200
here are surveillance photos from the hotel.

44
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:30,920
Notify Shao

45
00:03:30,920 --> 00:03:33,160
to do a DNA identification on the body.

46
00:03:34,800 --> 00:03:36,800
Lin, I told you.

47
00:03:38,960 --> 00:03:39,520
Shao is here.

48
00:03:39,520 --> 00:03:40,120
Shao.

49
00:03:40,360 --> 00:03:41,360
I collected them long ago.

50
00:03:41,360 --> 00:03:42,160
I was about to head back.

51
00:03:42,160 --> 00:03:42,720
Look.

52
00:03:43,200 --> 00:03:44,560
Have you found the cause of death?

53
00:03:44,560 --> 00:03:45,880
So far,

54
00:03:45,880 --> 00:03:48,600
we only found one trauma on the back of his head.

55
00:03:48,600 --> 00:03:50,079
There are no obvious signs of a struggle.

56
00:03:50,079 --> 00:03:51,800
And before he died,

57
00:03:51,800 --> 00:03:53,160
there were clear attempts to save himself.

58
00:03:53,160 --> 00:03:55,040
Judging from the bloody handprints on the bathtub,

59
00:03:55,040 --> 00:03:55,920
at least twice.

60
00:03:56,200 --> 00:03:57,160
So I think...

61
00:03:57,160 --> 00:03:58,960
He accidentally slipped when getting out of the bathtub,

62
00:03:58,960 --> 00:04:00,240
causing traumatic brain injury,

63
00:04:00,240 --> 00:04:01,440
and died of massive hemorrhage.

64
00:04:01,440 --> 00:04:02,480
When did you get here?

65
00:04:02,480 --> 00:04:03,360
Just now.

66
00:04:04,840 --> 00:04:06,170
He's always so elusive.

67
00:04:06,520 --> 00:04:07,160
Ignore him.

68
00:04:07,160 --> 00:04:07,880
Go on.

69
00:04:16,959 --> 00:04:18,440
According to the preliminary investigation,

70
00:04:18,440 --> 00:04:19,700
homicide is ruled out.

71
00:04:20,680 --> 00:04:21,940
Who reported it first?

72
00:04:22,120 --> 00:04:23,800
A cleaning lady named Liu Ying.

73
00:04:23,800 --> 00:04:24,640
Where is she?

74
00:04:25,200 --> 00:04:28,130
She was scared to death. She's calming down outside.

75
00:04:28,240 --> 00:04:30,200
Radiating your humanity again.

76
00:04:38,680 --> 00:04:39,560
Wow.

77
00:04:39,560 --> 00:04:40,840
He's really a talent.

78
00:04:44,280 --> 00:04:45,120
No.

79
00:04:47,560 --> 00:04:49,000
Isn't he hemophobic?

80
00:04:49,840 --> 00:04:51,480
The blood has dried, it's fine.

81
00:04:51,480 --> 00:04:52,120
Xiaobai.

82
00:04:52,760 --> 00:04:53,840
Are you done throwing up?

83
00:04:53,840 --> 00:04:55,240
If you are fine, help me take some notes.

84
00:04:55,240 --> 00:04:56,640
Okay.

85
00:05:00,320 --> 00:05:01,440
This young man,

86
00:05:01,440 --> 00:05:03,570
it's a pity he's not a forensic doctor.

87
00:05:03,720 --> 00:05:04,840
Let's go.

88
00:05:05,560 --> 00:05:06,960
Watch for a while longer.

89
00:05:11,120 --> 00:05:12,080
Hello, Officer.

90
00:05:13,280 --> 00:05:14,920
Hello. What's your name?

91
00:05:15,360 --> 00:05:15,960
Dong Shan.

92
00:05:16,240 --> 00:05:18,480
Hello. I'd like to ask you some questions.

93
00:05:18,480 --> 00:05:20,540
How long had the deceased lived here?

94
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:23,760
He was already here when I moved in.

95
00:05:23,760 --> 00:05:25,200
I'm not quite sure.

96
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:27,930
Do you have any strong impressions of him?

97
00:05:28,640 --> 00:05:29,680
Strong impressions?

98
00:05:29,680 --> 00:05:30,040
Oh.

99
00:05:30,360 --> 00:05:31,920
He had a big beard,

100
00:05:31,920 --> 00:05:32,680
was chubby,

101
00:05:32,680 --> 00:05:33,680
wore glasses,

102
00:05:33,680 --> 00:05:35,680
and liked to wear a top hat.

103
00:05:37,159 --> 00:05:39,159
He was about this tall.

104
00:05:41,680 --> 00:05:42,720
Is this

105
00:05:42,720 --> 00:05:44,250
the only door you have here?

106
00:05:45,159 --> 00:05:46,480
There's another one in the back.

107
00:05:46,480 --> 00:05:47,680
There's a back door?

108
00:05:48,720 --> 00:05:51,159
Did you notice if he usually interacted with anyone?

109
00:05:51,159 --> 00:05:53,220
Did anyone ever come looking for him?

110
00:05:54,400 --> 00:05:57,120
He rarely interacted with people.

111
00:05:57,120 --> 00:05:58,720
He didn't go out much either.

112
00:05:59,080 --> 00:06:00,120
Except for

113
00:06:00,120 --> 00:06:02,840
couriers or delivery guys dropping things off.

114
00:06:03,720 --> 00:06:04,480
Okay.

115
00:06:08,440 --> 00:06:09,160
Ma'am,

116
00:06:09,560 --> 00:06:10,820
I've brought him here.

117
00:06:11,440 --> 00:06:12,440
Hello, Officer.

118
00:06:12,440 --> 00:06:14,570
I'm the lobby manager of Xinmai Hotel.

119
00:06:14,680 --> 00:06:16,000
The deceased, Li Ting.

120
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:17,330
Did you know him before?

121
00:06:17,480 --> 00:06:18,560
Of course I do.

122
00:06:18,800 --> 00:06:20,800
He is a long-term guest of our hotel,

123
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:23,000
but he had a bit of a bad temper.

124
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:24,680
He's been dead for so long.

125
00:06:24,680 --> 00:06:26,040
How come no one noticed?

126
00:06:26,040 --> 00:06:27,970
Don't you usually clean the rooms?

127
00:06:28,440 --> 00:06:30,120
That was his own request.

128
00:06:30,120 --> 00:06:31,360
He said without his permission,

129
00:06:31,360 --> 00:06:32,720
we are not allowed to enter the room to clean.

130
00:06:32,720 --> 00:06:34,980
If he doesn't let you clean, you don't go?

131
00:06:35,800 --> 00:06:36,520
Well,

132
00:06:36,520 --> 00:06:37,980
you really can't blame us.

133
00:06:38,120 --> 00:06:39,980
Who would dare to ask for trouble?

134
00:06:40,520 --> 00:06:41,400
Before,

135
00:06:41,520 --> 00:06:44,080
he stayed in his room alone for a week.

136
00:06:44,480 --> 00:06:46,400
We were also worried about his safety,

137
00:06:46,400 --> 00:06:49,360
so we went in to take a look under the pretext of cleaning.

138
00:06:49,360 --> 00:06:51,600
But he kicked us out immediately.

139
00:06:54,360 --> 00:06:55,080
Manager,

140
00:06:55,080 --> 00:06:56,880
didn't he tell us not to knock?

141
00:06:57,320 --> 00:06:58,120
It's fine.

142
00:07:04,200 --> 00:07:05,280
Mr. Li,

143
00:07:05,280 --> 00:07:06,320
hello.

144
00:07:06,640 --> 00:07:08,680
You haven't left your room for a week.

145
00:07:08,680 --> 00:07:10,640
We're here to clean your room.

146
00:07:10,640 --> 00:07:11,640
Is it convenient?

147
00:07:17,480 --> 00:07:18,480
Are you there?

148
00:07:24,440 --> 00:07:25,440
What is it?

149
00:07:25,440 --> 00:07:25,880
Oh,

150
00:07:26,240 --> 00:07:28,500
room service here to change your towels.

151
00:07:28,600 --> 00:07:30,400
When did I call for room service?

152
00:07:32,240 --> 00:07:33,680
Mr. Li, you misunderstood.

153
00:07:33,680 --> 00:07:34,600
Our hotel must ensure

154
00:07:34,600 --> 00:07:35,680
the safety of our guests.

155
00:07:35,680 --> 00:07:36,960
You haven't left your room for a week.

156
00:07:36,960 --> 00:07:37,640
We were worried about you.

157
00:07:37,640 --> 00:07:38,960
What are you worried about?

158
00:07:38,960 --> 00:07:40,690
Are you worried I'd die inside?

159
00:07:40,880 --> 00:07:41,360
No.

160
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:43,760
Your hotel is really something.

161
00:07:43,760 --> 00:07:45,200
I told the front desk

162
00:07:45,200 --> 00:07:46,920
not to disturb me without my permission.

163
00:07:46,920 --> 00:07:47,720
Yes.

164
00:07:47,720 --> 00:07:49,120
If you keep disturbing me like this,

165
00:07:49,120 --> 00:07:50,080
how can I create?

166
00:07:50,800 --> 00:07:52,200
Sorry, sorry.

167
00:07:52,200 --> 00:07:52,920
Go.

168
00:07:52,920 --> 00:07:53,920
I'm sorry.

169
00:07:53,920 --> 00:07:55,120
Then have a good rest.

170
00:07:55,920 --> 00:07:57,320
Give me a bottle of water.

171
00:07:58,560 --> 00:07:59,360
Towel.

172
00:08:00,480 --> 00:08:01,240
Sorry.

173
00:08:01,240 --> 00:08:02,400
Have a good rest.

174
00:08:13,120 --> 00:08:14,650
Do you remember when it was?

175
00:08:15,720 --> 00:08:16,640
May 5th.

176
00:08:17,520 --> 00:08:19,050
You remember it so clearly.

177
00:08:20,280 --> 00:08:23,080
It was our first time getting scolded for worrying about a guest.

178
00:08:23,080 --> 00:08:24,480
How could I not remember?

179
00:08:25,240 --> 00:08:26,920
But he left the next day,

180
00:08:26,920 --> 00:08:29,760
and didn't return until half a month ago.

181
00:08:30,120 --> 00:08:31,240
During this time,

182
00:08:31,240 --> 00:08:33,840
aside from asking us to clean his room before he left,

183
00:08:33,840 --> 00:08:35,960
we never entered without permission.

184
00:08:35,960 --> 00:08:36,840
Our hotel

185
00:08:36,840 --> 00:08:39,770
highly respects the personal privacy of our guests.

186
00:08:40,760 --> 00:08:41,480
Xiaobai,

187
00:08:41,840 --> 00:08:42,640
verify this.

188
00:08:42,640 --> 00:08:43,480
Yes, ma'am.

189
00:08:45,160 --> 00:08:46,200
He rarely interacted with others.

190
00:08:46,200 --> 00:08:47,280
Lao Fang,

191
00:08:48,760 --> 00:08:49,520
I'm here.

192
00:08:50,160 --> 00:08:50,760
Okay, thank you.

193
00:08:50,760 --> 00:08:52,400
Go ahead with your work. I'll contact you if anything comes up.

194
00:08:52,400 --> 00:08:53,260
Okay, officer.

195
00:08:57,080 --> 00:08:58,240
I'm here, Captain Zhuang.

196
00:08:58,240 --> 00:09:00,760
Go and copy the surveillance footage as well.

197
00:09:00,760 --> 00:09:01,000
Okay.

198
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:02,000
Okay, come with me.

199
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:03,460
Yeah, sorry to bother you.

200
00:09:07,120 --> 00:09:07,960
Mr. Cheng.

201
00:09:08,280 --> 00:09:08,880
Mr. Cheng.

202
00:09:09,160 --> 00:09:10,560
We still need to collect evidence.

203
00:09:10,560 --> 00:09:12,360
You'll ruin the scene like this.

204
00:09:20,760 --> 00:09:21,560
Sir.

205
00:09:23,040 --> 00:09:23,600
Sir,

206
00:09:24,240 --> 00:09:25,120
please come out.

207
00:09:25,120 --> 00:09:26,360
You can't be in here.

208
00:09:37,480 --> 00:09:38,160
Sir.

209
00:09:39,040 --> 00:09:39,680
Sir,

210
00:09:39,680 --> 00:09:41,600
you can't touch this.

211
00:09:42,120 --> 00:09:42,800
Sir,

212
00:09:42,800 --> 00:09:44,200
Mr. Cheng, please don't.

213
00:09:49,360 --> 00:09:50,160
Put it down.

214
00:09:50,160 --> 00:09:51,360
I'm looking for evidence.

215
00:09:51,360 --> 00:09:52,520
Put it down.

216
00:09:53,400 --> 00:09:54,000
Oh.

217
00:09:59,320 --> 00:10:00,840
I could call you stupid,

218
00:10:00,840 --> 00:10:03,360
but your usual logical analysis skills are quite strong.

219
00:10:03,360 --> 00:10:04,800
But if I call you smart,

220
00:10:04,800 --> 00:10:07,480
you don't know how to be flexible at a time like this.

221
00:10:07,480 --> 00:10:10,680
This room has the exact same layout as room 208.

222
00:10:10,680 --> 00:10:13,400
If you really want to analyze something, do it here.

223
00:10:13,400 --> 00:10:15,360
Why do you have to go over there and cause trouble?

224
00:10:15,360 --> 00:10:16,160
Thank you.

225
00:10:16,160 --> 00:10:17,720
You actually know how to say thank you?

226
00:10:17,720 --> 00:10:19,520
I wasn't good with words before.

227
00:10:21,200 --> 00:10:24,240
You can use your divergent thinking now.

228
00:10:24,240 --> 00:10:25,440
Whatever you were thinking about just now,

229
00:10:25,440 --> 00:10:26,560
you can finish it here.

230
00:10:26,560 --> 00:10:27,200
Really.

231
00:10:46,520 --> 00:10:47,600
Stop.

232
00:10:50,360 --> 00:10:52,520
When someone is taking a shower,

233
00:10:52,520 --> 00:10:54,320
why would they pull the curtain?

234
00:10:54,720 --> 00:10:59,120
Even if he is someone who enjoys his private space,

235
00:10:59,120 --> 00:11:02,360
he would pull the curtain all the way.

236
00:11:03,640 --> 00:11:05,800
Do you remember at the crime scene,

237
00:11:05,800 --> 00:11:08,360
where this curtain was pulled to?

238
00:11:10,120 --> 00:11:11,280
I remember.

239
00:11:13,320 --> 00:11:15,680
He pulled it to here.

240
00:11:27,240 --> 00:11:27,840
Stop.

241
00:11:29,640 --> 00:11:30,840
While showering,

242
00:11:30,840 --> 00:11:33,040
people usually face the faucet

243
00:11:33,040 --> 00:11:34,760
because it's easier to reach things.

244
00:11:34,760 --> 00:11:38,520
But the gap in the curtain was facing the bed.

245
00:11:38,520 --> 00:11:39,320
That means

246
00:11:39,320 --> 00:11:42,250
there is something extremely important over there.

247
00:11:42,640 --> 00:11:44,560
But the door was locked from the inside at the time.

248
00:11:44,560 --> 00:11:46,280
What important thing did he have

249
00:11:46,280 --> 00:11:47,940
that he had to keep staring at?

250
00:11:50,400 --> 00:11:52,200
Or maybe something

251
00:11:52,200 --> 00:11:53,840
with a mind of its own?

252
00:11:55,480 --> 00:11:57,360
Perhaps a person.

253
00:11:57,920 --> 00:11:59,160
That makes sense.

254
00:12:02,280 --> 00:12:03,720
In that instant,

255
00:12:04,880 --> 00:12:06,210
the accident happened.

256
00:12:12,480 --> 00:12:13,560
He slipped

257
00:12:13,960 --> 00:12:15,490
and hit the back of his head.

258
00:12:15,600 --> 00:12:17,080
Stop.

259
00:12:18,760 --> 00:12:22,160
If he slipped and wanted to push himself up,

260
00:12:22,160 --> 00:12:24,640
he should have used his entire palm.

261
00:12:24,640 --> 00:12:25,720
But now,

262
00:12:25,720 --> 00:12:28,120
he was using his five fingertips.

263
00:12:28,560 --> 00:12:32,200
That means what he was trying to grab was

264
00:12:38,080 --> 00:12:41,210
someone who left him to die or took the chance to kill him.

265
00:12:42,240 --> 00:12:44,240
That person must have had a grudge against him.

266
00:12:44,240 --> 00:12:46,880
Good analysis, young man.

267
00:12:47,160 --> 00:12:49,560
The self-cultivation of a police officer.

268
00:12:49,640 --> 00:12:50,400
As expected,

269
00:12:50,400 --> 00:12:52,730
it's not as simple as an accidental death.

270
00:12:53,280 --> 00:12:55,560
Check the surveillance cameras outside carefully.

271
00:12:55,560 --> 00:12:57,000
There should be new discoveries.
